        <scopecontent id="ref69">
            <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
            <p>The Socialist Labor Party Printed Ephemera Collection spans the years 1883 to 1992 and consists of fliers, newspaper clippings, brochures, circular letters, pamphlets and convention proceedings and reports. Clippings and flyers pertainin to candidates and the party platform make up a significant part of the collection. Also included are some material from the National Executive Committee, minutes, publications and circular letters. A few state and local party records are included in the collection. The main SLP papers collection is housed at the University of Wisconsin.</p>
        </scopecontent>
